        "id": 1000009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T07:12:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This represents the same information twice? `iter` also (conceptually) contains a count (`entries`) and a `struct variable_field`.\n\nThe only concern is loss of information during iteration. But perhaps people wanting to iterate multiple times could either dynamically store the results from the first iteration, or re-decode the message buffer?",
      "revId": "a2f9c8ed32403586bfcbe614c52183aef790f585",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1796d12d_230bf467",
        "filename": "include/libpldm/platform.h",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 3211,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000926
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T09:29:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e The only concern is loss of information during iteration\n\nYes, I thought we need to save it, so we can iterate multiple times.\n\nThis iterator API is kinda new to me, I don\u0027t have any experience for designing or using such things, but here are some thoughts to your suggestions.\n\n\u003e But perhaps people wanting to iterate multiple times could either dynamically store the results from the first iteration or re-decode the message buffer?\n\nTo me it looks like going all over the full PDR again seems like a too expensive move. And it is not very intuitive for the user, that iteration can be performed only once on data.\n\nI remember I\u0027ve once asked you, is it okay, that we need to write that much of a boilerplate code in the library to implement this iterator api. And you\u0027ve answered that you don\u0027t mind having it, as long as API for the user is simple. I guess that idea stick with me. I think we shouldn\u0027t require the user to perform additional actions to make parsing permanent. It is not very obvious and gives some burden to the user, and the main point was to simplify things for the user.",
      "parentUuid": "aee6dcdf_cae7b0d6",
      "revId": "a2f9c8ed32403586bfcbe614c52183aef790f585",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1437f5f7_9dd7594f",
        "filename": "include/libpldm/platform.h",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 3211,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-17T00:01:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure, my query wasn\u0027t a direction to change it, more just to discuss such thoughts. Thanks for your input. I\u0027ll think about it more.",
      "parentUuid": "1796d12d_230bf467",
      "revId": "a2f9c8ed32403586bfcbe614c52183aef790f585",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7ecb2696_2943a4c8",
        "filename": "include/libpldm/platform.h",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 3247,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T07:12:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we\u0027re storing this then perhaps we don\u0027t need the two `info` arguments to `decode_pldm_platform_redfish_action_pdr()`? We could initialise the `info`s later with the information from an instance of this struct?",
      "revId": "a2f9c8ed32403586bfcbe614c52183aef790f585",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "205ea3a7_4c40540a",
        "filename": "include/libpldm/platform.h",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 3247,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000926
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-12T09:29:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I guess we can do something like that, but I don\u0027t think it would be fair/safe to ask the user to manually copy some fields from the `pldm_platform_redfish_action_pdr` to `pldm_platform_redfish_action_pdr_action_info`. So in this case we would need to introduce another API function to initialize the `pldm_platform_redfish_action_pdr_action_info` from  the `pldm_platform_redfish_action_pdr`. And I\u0027m not sure that will simplify things",
      "parentUuid": "7ecb2696_2943a4c8",
      "revId": "a2f9c8ed32403586bfcbe614c52183aef790f585",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
